  "title": "Senior Administrative Assistant (Office Hour/Healthcare/5days)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Administrative Assistant / Senior Administrative Assistant (Medical Records Office)</strong></h3><p>1-year contract (convertible to permanent)</p><p><strong>Role Summary:</strong><br />Provide administrative and operational support in the Medical Records Office, managing medical report requests while ensuring confidentiality, accuracy, and timely delivery.</p><p><strong>Key Duties:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Process medical report requests and payments</li><li>Retrieve, manage, and maintain medical records</li><li>Follow up with doctors and handle urgent cases</li><li>Liaise with internal and external stakeholders</li><li>Perform quality checks and prepare basic reports/statistics</li></ul></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p><ul><li>O-Level (Scanning & Records Management) / Diploma (Medical Reports)</li><li>Minimum 4 years’ experience in healthcare or service industry</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel and Word</li><li>Good communication and customer service skills</li><li>Able to work in a fast-paced environment</li></ul><p>📩 Apply now and grow your career in healthcare!</p><p>(Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)<br /></p><p><strong>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte</strong> Ltd I EA License No.: 12C6285<br />Lee Pui Shan I Reg. No: R25157211<br /><strong>Email CV to : </strong><a href=\"mailto:jessicalee@envirodynamics.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>jessicalee@envirodynamics.com.sg</strong><br /><br /></a><strong>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by company relating to this job application</strong></p></p>",
